[{"id":"VH979857","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents 2 diagrams which show a front view and a side view of a configuration of a wire and a magnet. The front view shows that in the central cavity of the magnet, a current carrying wire is suspended by two strings. In the side view, it is shown the magnet is in the shape of a C with square corners. The angle between both hanging strings and the vertical plane of the view is 12 degrees. A note states the figures are not drawn to scale.\" height=\"254\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH979857.g02.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A current-carrying wire is suspended between the poles of a permanent magnet by light strings, as shown in the front view figure. When the wire carries a current of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 microamperes\"><math alttext=\"3 microamperes\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>3</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, the string makes a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"12 degrees\"><math alttext=\"12 degrees\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>12</mn><mi>°</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> angle with the vertical, as shown in the side view figure. The length of the wire within the region of the magnetic field is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 centimeters\"><math alttext=\"10 centimeters\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mn>10</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following quantities should a student measure to determine the magnitude of the magnetic field between the poles of the magnet?</p>\n\n<ol class=\"ordered_list style:1\">\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Vertical distance between the poles of the magnet</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Mass of the wire</li>\n\t<li class=\"list_paragraph\">Length of the supporting strings</li>\n</ol>\n","rubricRef":"VH979857_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">I only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">II only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">III only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">I and II only</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">I, II, and III</p>"],"answer":1}]